<section class="newsletter" id="newsletter">
  <div class="newsletter-card">
    <div class="mono eyebrow">// weekly-ish, no spam</div>
    <h2 class="display">Don't get
      <span class="circled">automated.
        <svg viewBox="0 0 200 70" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true" class="draw-in">
          <path d="M20 38 C 22 15, 90 6, 140 12 C 185 17, 194 40, 168 54 C 138 68, 40 66, 22 50 C 8 38, 30 20, 60 16" fill="none" stroke="var(--red)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" pathLength="1"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
    </h2>
    <p>One email with what changed in AI this week, what it means for working designers, and one
       concrete thing to try. Written by a career designer turned product manager who's living
       the adaptation, not a content farm.</p>

    {# Submits into a hidden iframe (target="hidden_iframe") so the visitor never
       leaves the page for Google's own confirmation screen; the onsubmit handler
       swaps in our own "thanks" message after a short delay for the POST to land. #}
    <form class="signup" id="newsletter-form" action="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScsR6DVjl1MlrVb3YyA5g_1aMOLr21qYh4NSX03pFvoRv_mDg/formResponse" method="post" target="hidden_iframe" onsubmit="setTimeout(function () { document.getElementById('newsletter-form').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('newsletter-note').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('newsletter-thanks').style.display = 'block'; }, 300)">
      <input type="email" name="entry.872290881" placeholder="you@studio.com" aria-label="Email address" required>
      <button class="btn btn-ink" type="submit">Join the list</button>
    </form>
    <iframe name="hidden_iframe" style="display:none" aria-hidden="true"></iframe>

    <p id="newsletter-thanks" class="hand note" style="display:none">ps. you're on the list. first one lands next week.</p>
    <p id="newsletter-note" class="hand note">ps. it's free. your inbox will survive.</p>
  </div>
</section>
